A combined team, comprising of Raiders Squad, operatives from GRA Division and Area Command Asaba, led by the Area Crime officer, SP Kufre Udofia have arrested ten suspected cultists in Asaba, Delta State. The Police also recovered one fabricated AK47 rifle, charms, fake Vigilante ID card, and AC&DC black ice confraternity regalias. The suspects were arrested while planning to attack innocent citizens at Mile 5, a boundary between Oshimili North and Oshimili South Local Government Areas. The Delta State Police Command, led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said, “investigation is ongoing.”